This paper discusses a semi-supervised model of peer review that aims to improve the traditional approach. The paper focuses on evaluating the potential advantages of such a system, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and cryptography (cs.CR).
